ADF ERRORS-TELEKOM PROJECT
------------------
1-TRIGGER PROBLEMS
------------------
We faced an overlapping trigger issue in which the next scheduled pipeline started while the previous broadband usage load was still running. This caused both runs to process the same business date. We identified it through ADF Monitor and our audit table. We cancelled the duplicate run and cleaned its partial output. To prevent recurrence, we introduced pipeline concurrency control and a control-table check that blocks a second run for the same entity and business date.
01:00 AM → First pipeline started
02:00 AM → First pipeline was still running
02:00 AM → Second pipeline started

This caused:

Duplicate processing
High load on Oracle
High load on Self-hosted IR
Two runs writing into the same ADLS path
Incorrect audit and watermark values

How we overcame it
We took the following actions:

Cancelled the duplicate pipeline run.
Checked whether it had already written any data.
Removed or quarantined partial output from the second run.
Continued the original pipeline.
Performed row-count reconciliation after completion.

Permanent prevention
We introduced a control-table check at the beginning of the pipeline:

Lookup existing run
        ↓
Is the same entity and business date already running?
        ↓
Yes → Stop or skip the new run
No  → Start processing

pipeline:
Trigger starts pipeline
        ↓
Lookup existing active run
        ↓
If Condition
   ├── Active run exists
   │       ↓
   │   Skip or Fail pipeline
   │
   └── No active run
           ↓
       Create InProgress record
           ↓
       Execute ingestion
           ↓
       Update status to Succeeded/Failed
