3. Linked Service connection problems
-------------------------------------
In our project, all Oracle ingestion pipelines suddenly failed because the Oracle password had expired.
The Oracle Linked Service was retrieving the password from Azure Key Vault, but the secret had not been updated after the password change.
The pipelines failed with an error similar to:
Invalid username or password
Login denied
Authentication failed

How we identified it
We:
Opened the failed Copy Activity in ADF Monitor.
Checked the activity error.
Tested the Oracle Linked Service connection.
Confirmed that the same Linked Service was used by all failed pipelines.
Checked the Key Vault secret version.
Coordinated with the Oracle team to confirm the password change.

Because many pipelines failed at the same time with the same authentication error, it indicated a shared connection problem rather than a table-specific issue.
How we overcame it
We:
Obtained the updated Oracle credential through the approved process.
Updated the Key Vault secret.
Retested the Linked Service.
Reran the failed ingestion pipelines using the original business date and batch window.
Verified that no partial data had been left behind.
