7.Get Metadata and file-arrival problems
----------------------------------------
Get Metadata Activity checks information about files and folders, such as:
Whether a file exists
File size
Last-modified time
Child files inside a folder

In our project, an hourly broadband-fault file was processed before the source system finished uploading it.
For example, the complete file should contain one million records. ADF detected the file as soon as it appeared in the folder, but only 300,000 records had been uploaded at that time.
The pipeline technically succeeded, but the data was incomplete.
How we identified it
We observed:
Source count: 1,000,000
ADF copied count: 300,000
File size was lower than expected
The file’s modification time kept changing
The trigger started as soon as the file appeared
This was a silent data issue because the ADF activity itself did not necessarily fail.
How we overcame it
We used a completion-marker approach.
The source system first uploads the data file:broadband_faults_20260720_1000.csv
After the file is fully uploaded, it creates:broadband_faults_20260720_1000.done
ADF checks for the .done file using Get Metadata.
Get Metadata on .done file
        ↓
Does it exist?
        ├── Yes → Process the data file
        └── No  → Wait and check again
		
We also checked:
File exists
File size is greater than zero
Expected file name is present
File has stopped changing
File has not already been processed

Missing-file scenario
If the file is expected by 2:00 AM but is not available:
Get Metadata
    ↓
File does not exist
    ↓
Wait 10 minutes
    ↓
Check again

After a limited number of checks, the pipeline:
Records the file as late or missing.
Fails the ingestion stage.
Sends an alert.
Does not start downstream processing.

